Overview:
  - To deploy jar to remote machine
  - To setup a service for the running the Jar
  - Start the service
  - Wait for the service to start

Steps:
  - Copy a Jar from Jenkins to the remote machine.
  - Copy the init/service script for running the Jar as service.
  - Start the service, by executing the service. The service will be executed as the user specified in the init script.
  - Check the port on which the service (jar) is listening.

Supported Platform:
  - Currently the init script works only on the Ubuntu 14.04, not tested in Ubuntu 16+ and on rpm based linux systems.

